ings. Experimental results show that 1)\nStacked BNAS obtains better performance than BNAS-v2 on both CIFAR-10 and\nImageNet, 2) the proposed KES algorithm contributes to reducing the parameters\nof the learned architecture with satisfactory performance, and 3) Stacked BNAS\ndelivers a state-of-the-art efficiency of 0.02 GPU days.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 Nov 2021 12:49:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 26 Jul 2022 11:29:35 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 27 Jul 2022 03:37:38 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 1 Aug 2022 14:23:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-02"}
